-- Suntech Expects 2011 Solar Panel Sales to Increase 20 Percent
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   M a r t i n
-- 2010-12-06T14:57:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-06/suntech-expects-2011-solar-panel-sales-to-increase-20-raises-guidance.html
Suntech Power Holdings Co. , China’s
largest solar panel maker, expects sales to climb at least 20
percent next year and plans to increase production capacity to
meet surging demand.  Revenue next year will be $3.4 billion to $3.6 billion, up
from revised 2010 guidance of $2.78 billion to $2.83 billion,
the Wuxi, China-based company said today in a statement.
Production capacity will climb to 2,400 megawatts by the end of
next year from 1,800 megawatts at the end of this year.  Suntech gained 24 cents, or 2.9 percent, to $8.52 at 9:53
a.m. in New York Stock Exchange composite trading. The  stock  has
dropped 49 percent this year.  (Suntech plans to discuss its forecast at an investor
meeting in New York today at 10 a.m. To listen to a webcast, go
to the company’s website  http://www.suntech-power.com/ )  To contact the reporter on this story:
